論文中文名稱：擴增實境遊戲結合古典小說之研究與創作－－以《西遊記》為例
														[以論文名稱查詢館藏系統]
													


論文英文名稱：A Study and Creation on Applying Augmented Reality Games to Classic Novels —— A Case Study of ‘Journey to West’
														[以論文名稱查詢館藏系統]
													


院校名稱：臺北科技大學


學院名稱：設計學院


系所名稱：互動媒體設計研究所


畢業學年度：105


畢業學期：第二學期


出版年度：106


中文姓名：譚聖音


英文姓名：Sheng-Yin Tan


研究生學號：104AC8018


學位類別：碩士


口試日期：20170717


論文頁數：123


指導教授中文名：李來春


指導教授英文名：Lai-Chung Lee


口試委員中文名：葛如均；王聖銘；盧姝如


口試委員英文名：Ju-Chun Ko；Sheng-Ming Wang；Shu-Ru Lu


中文關鍵詞：擴增實境
																；
																電子遊戲
																；
																遊戲流暢體驗
																；
																中國古典小說
																；
																《西遊記》


英文關鍵詞：Augmented Reality
																；
																Video Game
																；
																Game Flow
																；
																Chinese Classic Novel
																；
																Journey to West


論文中文摘要：近年來科技不斷發展，擴增實境技術已經越來越進入我們的生活、教育、建築、娛樂等各個方面；與此同時，作為古人智慧代表的古典小說影響力日漸式微。本研究希望結合新科技新媒體與古典小說，運用擴增實境技術的有趣互動，創作一款遊戲，令玩家透過擴增實境遊戲的方式，瞭解回憶古典小說《西遊記》，讓擴增實境遊戲成為《西遊記》的展示形式。本研究依據「遊戲流暢體驗的理論」作為遊戲設計的標準，將古典小說按照文學改編遊戲的方式進行遊戲策劃和開發，令情境更加真實化，小說能夠以更加真實自然的方式呈現給玩家。本創作「AR西遊」結合實體模型展示小說《西遊記》之場景，並結合七巧板遊戲令玩家破解謎題，幫助擴增實境中的遊戲主角經歷小說故事，破關取經。後期開發完成後，已於展場進行展覽與實驗施測。透過觀察與問捲的方式蒐集測試者操作資訊與意見回饋，實際有效問捲30份；問捲主要採用遊戲流暢體驗(GameFlow)量表進行檢測，統計分析顯示受測者皆有達到較高程度的遊戲流暢體驗，並且不同年齡間距、性別的玩家在不同向度受到影響。最後研究者回顧本研究之創作，並總結提出擴增實境結合古典小說開發遊戲之設計方法對於未來相關應用創作之參考方向。


論文英文摘要：In recent years, with the continuous development of science and technology, augmented reality technology becomes more and more important in our daily lives, education, architecture, entertainment and other fields. At the same time, as a presentation of traditional wisdom, the influence of classical novels is decreasing. Aiming to combine new technology and media with classic novels, this research created a game with augmented reality technology where players could know about or review the classic novel Journey to the West. In this way, the augmented reality game became the illustration of the novel. With a game-designing measure derived from the GameFlow theory, this research designed and developed a game in a typical method of adapting games from literature so that the environment could be more realistic and the novel can be presented to players in a more figurative way. The work AR Journey displays scenes from the novel with a physical model, let players solve challenges built with tangram and motivates them to help the main character go through the storyline and obtain Buddhist texts.After game development, the game was displayed in an exhibition and an experimental survey was conducted. Test information and feedback was obtained with observation and survey. 30 effective questionnaires were collected. The questionnaire used metrics mainly from the GameFlow theory for measurement. Statistical analysis showedthat players had reached a high level of game flow, and players of different ages and genders were affected in different dimensions. Finally, the researcher reviewed the process of the research and concluded a method of combining classical novels with augmented reality games as a reference for future development of related applications.


